amdgpu: uvd_v4_2 — A18 soft-fail UVD hw_init so amdgpu probe survives

After 17 iterations of UVD bring-up, the failure is structurally
blocked by Sony's SBL/SAMU access requirements (see
checkpoint/docs/research/orbis-dungeon/rooms/sbl-driver.md). The
SAMU runs Sony's signed firmware, holds exclusive SMU access, and
Linux has no SBL driver. UVD VCPU stays stuck waiting for chip
state we cannot replicate.

The previous behavior: hw_init returns -ETIMEDOUT (or -110 from
ring_test), which kills amdgpu probe entirely. Result: no DRM, no
display, Hyprland dies with SIGABRT, "white screen" because HDMI
bridge is driven but desktop never composes.

A18: change uvd_v4_2_hw_init to return 0 even when start_liverpool
or ring_test fails. amdgpu thinks UVD initialized OK; rest of
amdgpu (DRM/display/GFX/SDMA) continues. UVD itself is
non-functional but anything that doesn't try to USE UVD works fine.

Userspace consequence: video decode falls back to software (libavcodec
/ vp9 / etc.). Acceptable trade for a working desktop on PS4 Linux.

Expected hardware signals:

  ✅ amdgpu probe completes (no "Fatal error during GPU init")
  ✅ DRM connector ps4_bridge populates HDMI-A-1
  ✅ Hyprland (or any DRM compositor) starts and composes desktop
  ✅ HDMI displays the Linux desktop
  🟡 UVD broken — confirmed by DRM_WARN at hw_init time
  ❌ amdgpu still dies — something else is blocking; investigate
     subsequent error in dmesg

Combined with v76e-A17 (skip STATUS poll, fall through to ring init)
this gives clean "UVD failed gracefully" semantics.

Signed-off-by: Meerzulee <mirzaali@screeninternational.org>

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/uvd_v4_2.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/uvd_v4_2.c
@@ -196,8 +196,33 @@
 	amdgpu_ring_commit(ring);
 
 done:
-	if (!r)
+	if (!r) {
 		DRM_INFO("UVD initialized successfully.\n");
+	} else {
+		/*
+		 * v76e-A18: UVD soft-fail. After 17 iterations, UVD bring-up
+		 * is structurally blocked on chip state set during Orbis
+		 * runtime that we can't replicate without SBL/SMU access.
+		 *
+		 * Returning the error from hw_init kills amdgpu probe entirely
+		 * — no DRM, no display, no Hyprland. Returning 0 here lets the
+		 * rest of amdgpu (DRM/display/GFX/SDMA) continue. UVD itself
+		 * is non-functional but anything that doesn't try to USE UVD
+		 * works fine.
+		 *
+		 * Userspace consequence: video decode falls back to software
+		 * (libavcodec / vp9 / etc.). Acceptable trade for having a
+		 * working desktop on PS4 Linux.
+		 *
+		 * If you actually need hardware video decode on PS4, see
+		 * checkpoint/docs/research/orbis-dungeon/rooms/sbl-driver.md
+		 * for the structural reason this is blocked.
+		 */
+		DRM_WARN("ps4 uvd: hw_init failed (%d) — soft-failing per "
+			 "v76e-A18 to let amdgpu probe continue. UVD is "
+			 "non-functional; software video decode only.\n", r);
+		r = 0;
+	}
 
 	return r;
 }
